om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Private credit</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just from first principles it is weird=
 that, if you are a company or a private equity sponsor looking to borrow a=
 lot of money, and you go to a gigantic bank like J.P. Morgan Chase &amp; C=
o., the bank will say =E2=80=9Cyes, I would be happy to help you find that =
money.=E2=80=9D Whereas if you go to an alternative asset manager like Blue=
 Owl Capital or Ares Management Corp., the alternative asset manager will p=
ull out a bag with a dollar sign on it and say =E2=80=9Cyes, here is=C2=A0m=
oney.=E2=80=9D If you asked the average person =E2=80=9Cwho has more money,=
 JPMorgan Chase or Blue Owl,=E2=80=9D they would probably say =E2=80=9CI gu=
ess the biggest bank in America has more money than a company I have never =
heard of.=E2=80=9D Also they would be right! JPMorgan has <a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35478826.261334/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2V=
jLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTk2MTcvMDAwMDAxOTYxNzI0MDAwMz=
I2L2pwbS0yMDI0MDMzMS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9c076bbd" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">$4 tri=
llion of assets</a>; Blue Owl manages <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/35478826.261334/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0F=
yY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTgyMzk0NS8wMDAxODIzOTQ1MjQwMDAwNDEvb3dsLTIwMjQwMz=
MxLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC5221ec19" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">about $174 billion</a>.=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And yet from the perspective of a pr=
ivate equity sponsor, JPMorgan is in the business of=C2=A0<em>intermediatin=
g loans:=C2=A0</em>When you go to a big bank to get financing for a leverag=
ed buyout, the bank will work with you to market the debt and find investor=
s to buy it; you don=E2=80=99t expect the bank to buy most of the debt itse=
lf.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tr=
ansparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Whereas Blue Owl is in the business of=C2=A0<em>providing loans: =
</em>You go to a private credit manager because you expect it to just hand =
you the money. Obviously it too is an intermediary =E2=80=94=C2=A0that mone=
y doesn=E2=80=99t just=C2=A0<em>belong=C2=A0</em>to Blue Owl; that money is=
 in funds that it manages on behalf of other investors =E2=80=94=C2=A0but i=
t can give you the money much more directly.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">This is sort of an unusual equilibrium. Once upon a time, if you went to =
a bank for a loan, the bank would either give you the loan (from its own ba=
lance sheet), or it would refuse to give you the loan, and there was not a =
ton of competition from other lenders. Over time, the modern world of syndi=
cated leveraged lending grew up, so that in, like, 2014, if you went to a b=
ank for financing for a leveraged buyout, it would work with you on a marke=
ting process to sell loans and bonds to investors. This was nice for the ba=
nks =E2=80=94=C2=A0they got fees while using less balance sheet and taking =
less long-term risk =E2=80=94=C2=A0and probably did expand the amount of cr=
edit they could provide. (If you went to a bank in 1954 to ask for a loan t=
o fund a large leveraged buyout, it would have just said =E2=80=9Cno.=E2=80=
=9D) You=E2=80=99d ask for money, the bank would come up with a plan to rai=
se the money, the plan would generally succeed,=C2=A0and you=E2=80=99d be l=
ike =E2=80=9Cyes, thanks, this is good service.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">But then in recent years private credit emerged as an alterna=
tive to the syndicated market. For borrowers, it has some drawbacks. (It=E2=
=80=99s generally more expensive, and also, if you want a big loan, you mig=
ht have to negotiate with multiple private lenders, instead of having one b=
ank to run the syndication process.) But as a matter of customer service th=
e appeal is obvious: It is fast and certain. They just give you the money.<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are various possible ways for the ban=
ks to respond to this competitive pressure =E2=80=94=C2=A0improve pricing, =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35478826.261334/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMjEvYmFua3MtY=
XJlLW5vdy10YXJnZXRpbmctc29tZS1vZi1wcml2YXRlLWNyZWRpdC1zLXJpc2tpZXN0LWRlYnQ_=
Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyMzI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5=
ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNTIzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cBc8c916a7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">take on more risk</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=
=A0but the obvious, obvious, obvious one is =E2=80=9Cjust give them the mon=
ey.=E2=80=9D If a private equity sponsor goes to JPMorgan looking to borrow=
 money for a buyout, JPMorgan could just pull out a bag of money and give i=
t to them. JPMorgan has a lot of money!</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of =
course there are details to take care of here, and in practice, for capital=
 and regulatory reasons,=C2=A0JPMorgan <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/35478826.261334/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDIvdGhlLWJhbmtzLWFyZS13aGVyZS10aGUtbW9uZXkta=
XNuLXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyMzI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291=
cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNTIzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd7baafa8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">might be wary of lending from its =
balance sheet</a> and more interested in intermediating these loans the way=
 private credit firms do, by raising money from investors and pooling it to=
 make loans. But the big banks mostly do have asset management arms, so tha=
t is a possibility.=C2=A0In modern terms, =E2=80=9CJPMorgan just lending th=
e money=E2=80=9D is called =E2=80=9Cbanks getting into private credit=E2=80=
=9D rather than, like, =E2=80=9Cbanks being banks.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Still,=C2=A0banks are definitely getting into private cred=
it. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/35478826.261334/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMjMvanBtb3JnYW4taHVudHMtZm9yLXByaXZhdGUtY3JlZGl0LWZpcm0tZm9=
yLWFzc2V0LW1hbmFnZW1lbnQtYXJtP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MjMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZW=
RpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDUyMyZ1dG1fY2Ftc=
GFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBde76a8bc" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Hannah Lev=
itt and Paula Seligson report</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. is on the hunt to buy a private credit firm to=
 augment its $3.6 trillion asset management arm, as the biggest US bank mak=
es more inroads into Wall Street=E2=80=99s buzziest sector.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">The JPMorgan unit is seeking a private credit shop that co=
uld bolster its private capital business, according to people familiar with=
 the matter. As part of the effort, the company held talks to buy Chicago-b=
ased Monroe Capital this year, but the two firms ultimately decided not to =
