ding US insurers exposed to Everton football club bidder 777 Partners.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The agency is arguing in a New Jersey court tha=
t it has a First Amendment right to publish its opinion on a company=E2=80=
=99s financial strength, after two US insurers accused it of using=C2=A0=E2=
=80=9Cflawed methods, improper assumptions, and demonstrably false data=E2=
=80=9D to downgrade them.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe life=
blood of AM Best=E2=80=99s business is its credibility, and that credibilit=
y is irreparably damaged when it is prevented from publishing its opinions =
about an insurer=E2=80=99s creditworthiness to the public, even if, and oft=
en times especially when, that opinion is negative,=E2=80=9D the rating age=
ncy argued in a response filed with the court this week.</p></blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/35478826.261334/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudH=
